The paper deals with deep learning approaches to anomaly detection, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of entropy and information theory, which are topics that fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a new methodology for deep semi-supervised anomaly detection, which is a topic that falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
